.TH start-cli-backup-job-edit 1  "edit " 
.SH NAME
start\-cli\-backup\-job\-edit \- Edit an automatic backup job
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBstart\-cli backup job edit\fR [\fB\-\-name\fR] [\fB\-\-cron\fR] [\fB\-\-timezone\fR] [\fB\-\-all\-services\fR] [\fB\-\-package\-ids\fR] [\fB\-\-exclude\-package\-ids\fR] [\fB\-\-keep\-rule\fR] [\fB\-\-latest\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-service\-keep\-rule\fR] [\fB\-\-service\-latest\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-use\-default\-retention\fR] [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIID\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Edit an automatic backup job
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-name\fR \fI<NAME>\fR
Human\-readable automatic backup job name
.TP
\fB\-\-cron\fR \fI<CRON>\fR
Five\-field cron schedule (minute, hour, day of month, month, weekday)
.TP
\fB\-\-timezone\fR \fI<TIMEZONE>\fR
IANA timezone for the automatic backup schedule
.TP
\fB\-\-all\-services\fR
Back up every current and future service
.TP
\fB\-\-package\-ids\fR \fI<PACKAGE_IDS>\fR
Package IDs to include in the automatic backup
.TP
\fB\-\-exclude\-package\-ids\fR \fI<EXCLUDE_PACKAGE_IDS>\fR
Package IDs to exclude from current and future services
.TP
\fB\-\-keep\-rule\fR \fI<INTERVAL:COVERAGE>\fR
Version\-history rule INTERVAL:COVERAGE; accepts s, m, h, d, or w and may repeat
.TP
\fB\-\-latest\-only\fR
Keep only the latest automatic checkpoint
.TP
\fB\-\-service\-keep\-rule\fR \fI<PACKAGE_ID=INTERVAL:COVERAGE>\fR
Per\-service version\-history rule PACKAGE_ID=INTERVAL:COVERAGE; may repeat
.TP
\fB\-\-service\-latest\-only\fR \fI<PACKAGE_ID>\fR
Service package IDs that should keep only their latest checkpoint
.TP
\fB\-\-use\-default\-retention\fR \fI<PACKAGE_ID>\fR
Service package IDs that should use the job\*(Aqs default retention
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR

.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIID\fR>
Automatic backup job identifier
